00:06:32.005 --> 00:06:34.242
As to the opera itself, well,

80
00:06:34.242 --> 00:06:39.588
let's first have an explanation of
the style of singing calling monody.

81
00:06:39.588 --> 00:06:45.740
Expressive one line monody solo singing
accompanied by a small ensemble.

82
00:06:45.740 --> 00:06:50.780
Eventually, early monody would bifurcate
into two contrasting modes of delivery,

83
00:06:50.780 --> 00:06:52.860
recitative and aria.

84
00:06:52.860 --> 00:06:55.380
What the difference between
a recitative and an aria?

85
00:06:55.380 --> 00:06:59.530
Well recitative generally told what
was going on, what's happening, and

86
00:06:59.530 --> 00:07:05.930
aria reflected what the protagonist,
the singer, felt about what was happening.

87
00:07:07.460 --> 00:07:12.560
You can find almost all of
Monteverdi's Orfeo on YouTube.

88
00:07:12.560 --> 00:07:13.820
But let's cut to the high point.

89
